 affected range of movement, or the absence of limbs.\", \"from\": 748, \"to\": 873, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 748, \"end\": 750, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Apple_silicon\", \"score\": 0.9999348651303703, \"rank\": 5.370179792753207e-05, \"text\": \"W1\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Apple_silicon\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Apple_silicon\"}, {\"begin\": 751, \"end\": 765, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shaun_Anderson\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Shaun Anderson\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shaun_Anderson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shaun_Anderson\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"These archers all shoot from seated and create their own style in pulling the bow back and aiming.\", \"from\": 874, \"to\": 972, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"T11 Louzanne Coetzee (1500m and marathon)  Runners with a near-total visual impairment.\", \"from\": 974, \"to\": 1061, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 978, \"end\": 994, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Louzanne_Coetzee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Louzanne Coetzee\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Louzanne_Coetzee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Louzanne_Coetzee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Some can make out an object at 25cm but all compete with a sighted guide runner.\", \"from\": 1062, \"to\": 1142, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"T12 Jaco Smit (100m)  Vision is constricted to a radius of less than five degrees and/or the ability to recognise a moving object at a distance of one metre.\", \"from\": 1144, \"to\": 1301, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"T37 Sheryl James (100m, 200m, 400m), Liezel Gouws (400m and long jump)  Athletes with movement and coordination moderately affected down one side.\", \"from\": 1303, \"to\": 1449, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1307, \"end\": 1319, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sheryl_James\", \"score\": 0.862068623756732, \"rank\": 0.16000000000000425, \"text\": \"Sheryl James\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q36180\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sheryl_James\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sheryl_James\"}, {\"begin\": 1340, \"end\": 1352, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Liezel_Gouws\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Liezel Gouws\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Liezel_Gouws\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Liezel_Gouws\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They have to compensate for asymmetry in the start, stride and overall power distribution.\", \"from\": 1450, \"to\": 1540, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"T38 Simone Kruger (discus)  Athletes with movement and coordination affected to a low degree in the lower trunk and legs, down one side or the whole body.\", \"from\": 1542, \"to\": 1696, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1542, \"end\": 1545, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Allison_T38\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.96661687508839e-15, \"text\": \"T38\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Allison_T38\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Allison_T38\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They show asymmetry and slightly reduced co-ordination of muscle movement.\", \"from\": 1697, \"to\": 1771, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Their running style is smoothed out as they increase in speed.\", \"from\": 1772, \"to\": 1834, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"T44 Mpumelelo Mhlongo (100m and long jump), Tezna Abrahams (long jump and 200m)  Athletes with movement affected at a low or moderate degree in one lower leg.\", \"from\": 1836, \"to\": 1994, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"They have unaffected knee joints allowing for controlled power delivery but they must focus harder to sense and grip the track surface.\", \"from\": 1995, \"to\": 2130, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"T46 Khumo Pitso (high jump)  Runners with movement moderately or highly affected in one or both arms or the absence of limbs.\", \"from\": 2132, \"to\": 2257, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2136, \"end\": 2141, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Huma_bird\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Khumo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Huma_bird\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Huma_bird\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"These athletes generate drive almost exclusively using the legs with reduced counterbalance from the arms.\", \"from\": 2258, \"to\": 2364, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"T47 Collen Mahlalela (400m)  Runners with movement affected at a low to moderate degree in one arm or the absence of limbs.\", \"from\": 2366, \"to\": 2489, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2370, \"end\": 2376, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Collen\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Collen\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Collen\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Collen\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They adjust for asymmetric upper body balance.\", \"from\": 2490, \"to\": 2536, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"T62 Paul Daniels (400m), Daniel du Plessis (400m)  Athletes with the absence of both legs below the knee.\", \"from\": 2538, \"to\": 2643, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2542, \"end\": 2554, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paul_Daniels\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.056617300078137e-24, \"text\": \"Paul Daniels\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paul_Daniels\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paul_Daniels\"}, {\"begin\": 2563, \"end\": 2580, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dan_du_Plessis\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Daniel du Plessis\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dan_du_Plessis\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dan_du_Plessis\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"All have difficulty accelerating out of the blocks.\", \"from\": 2644, \"to\": 2695, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"T63 Puseletso Mabote (100m and long jump)  Runners with the absence of one leg above the knee.\", \"from\": 2697, \"to\": 2791, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2711, \"end\": 2717, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mabote\", \"score\": 0.9998791767130828, \"rank\": 0.00012083788713701799, \"text\": \"Mabote\", \"types\": [\"Q532\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mabote\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mabote\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"All have difficulty accelerating out of the blocks.\", \"from\": 2792, \"to\": 2843, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"F12 Hermanus Blom (shot put)  Field athletes with a visual impairment.\", \"from\": 2845, \"to\": 2915, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2845, \"end\": 2848, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Factor_XII\", \"score\": 0.9994845748560935, \"rank\": 0.0005156909440521044, \"text\": \"F12\", \"types\": [\"Q7187\", \"Q206229\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Factor_XII\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Factor_XII\"}, {\"begin\": 2849, \"end\": 2857, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hermanus\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.835987409476371e-18, \"text\": \"Hermanus\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hermanus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hermanus\"}, {\"begin\": 2858, \"end\": 2862, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/August_Blom\", \"score\": 0.9998929705571464, \"rank\": 0.00010704066185574643, \"text\": \"Blom\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/August_Blom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/August_Blom\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"These throwers have a moderate visual impairment.\", \"from\": 2916, \"to\": 2965, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"They have a restricted field of view or their central vision is a blur.\", \"from\": 2966, \"to\": 3037, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"F44 Yane van der Merwe (discus)  Field athletes with available movement moderately affected in one lower leg.\", \"from\": 3039, \"to\": 3148, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3039, \"end\": 3042, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/T44_(classification)\", \"score\": 0.6969891087587383, \"rank\": 0.37837009803929345, \"text\": \"F44\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/T44_(classification)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/T44_(classification)\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"These athletes have to adjust for asymmetric balance; in the run-up javelin, and across the throwing circle in shot out and discus.\", \"from\": 3149, \"to\": 3280, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"F46 Kerwin Noemdo (shot put)  Field athletes with moderately affected movement in one or both arms or the absence of limbs.\", \"from\": 3282, \"to\": 3405, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3282, \"end\": 3285, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BMW_2_Series_Active_Tourer\", \"score\": 0.9986546712312504, \"rank\": 0.0012631106462862884, \"text\": \"F46\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BMW_2_Series_Active_Tourer\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BMW_2_Series_Active_Tourer\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"These athletes have to transmit power from hips and legs into the throw.\", \"from\": 3406, \"to\": 3478, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"BC3 Karabo Cassius Morapedi and Elanza Jordaan  Competitors with movement moderately affected in the trunk and to a high degree in the limbs.\", \"from\": 3480, \"to\": 3621, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3480, \"end\": 3483, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BC3\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.2491648097656295e-26, \"text\": \"BC3\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BC3\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BC3\"}, {\"begin\": 3484, \"end\": 3490, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australopithecus_sediba\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Karabo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australopithecus_sediba\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australopithecus_sediba\"}, {\"begin\": 3519, \"end\": 3526, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jordaan\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Jordaan\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jordaan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jordaan\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Athletes use a ramp to deliver the ball onto the court via a mouth pointer, head pointer or finger release.\", \"from\": 3622, \"to\": 3729, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"H1 Pieter du Preez  Hand cyclists that have highly affected movement in the trunk, legs and hands.\", \"from\": 3731, \"to\": 3829, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"All generate power just using their upper arms and shoulders.\", \"from\": 3830, \"to\": 3891, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Some may use devices to assist with grip.\", \"from\": 3892, \"to\": 3933, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"G4 (GIV) Philippa Johnson-Dwyer  Riders with low to moderate level of coordination, moderately affected movement in the hip joint, the absence of limbs, or a near-total visual impairment.\", \"from\": 3935, \"to\": 4122, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3944, \"end\": 3952, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Philippa_of_Hainault\", \"score\": 0.9999996865090489, \"rank\": 3.1075540908570415e-07, \"text\": \"Philippa\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Philippa_of_Hainault\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Philippa_of_Hainault\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"These riders are capable of circling and changes of pace at walk, trot and canter.\", \"from\": 4123, \"to\": 4205, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"J1 Ndyeni Lamani (under 73kg)  For visually impaired athletes.\", \"from\": 4207, \"to\": 4269, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"They begin each fight in a hold and must not move outside of the mat, though completely blind fighters are allowed occasional steps outside.\", \"from\": 4270, \"to\": 4410, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"PTS4 Kirsty Weir  Triathletes have coordination affected at a low-level on one side, at a high degree in one arm, or the absence of limbs.\", \"from\": 4412, \"to\": 4550, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In the swim all have a reduction of power.\", \"from\": 4551, \"to\": 4593, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In the cycle PTS4's tend to either have good power but reduced control or vice-versa.\", \"from\": 4594, \"to\": 4679, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In the run all compensate for imbalance and asymmetry.\", \"from\": 4680, \"to\": 4734, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"S5 Kat Swanepoel (50m backstroke, 100m freestyle, 200m freestyle)  Swimmers with co-ordination moderately affected, movement highly affected in the mid-trunk and legs, or the absence of limbs.\", \"from\": 4736, \"to\": 4928, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"These swimmers have difficulty holding good body position or swimming straight.\", \"from\": 4929, \"to\": 5008, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"SB4 Kat Swanepoel (100m breaststroke)  Breaststroke swimmers with co-ordination affected to a moderate degree in the whole body, or to a high degree in the trunk and legs.\", \"from\": 5010, \"to\": 5181, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5010, \"end\": 5013, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2015_IPC_Swimming_World_Championships_\\u2013_Men's_100_metre_breaststroke\", \"score\": 0.4860335195531305, \"rank\": 0.672413793103354, \"text\": \"SB4\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2015_IPC_Swimming_World_Championships_\\u2013_Men's_100_metre_breaststroke\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2015_IPC_Swimming_World_Championships_\\u2013_Men's_100_metre_breaststroke\"}, {\"begin\": 5014, \"end\": 5017, \"